        <article>
            <h1>Welcome to Embedded Server Pages</h1>
            <section>
                <p>ESP is a powerful "C"-based web framework for blazing fast dynamic web applications.
                It has an page templating engine, layout pages, a Model-View-Controller framework,
                    embedded database, content caching and application generator.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Quick Start</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li><b>Create ESP Pages</b>
                    <p>Create web pages under the "contents" directory.
                        Modify the layout in "layouts/default.html.exp" and customize the Less-based style sheet
                        in the "contents/css/app.less" and "contents/css/theme.less".</p>
                    </li>

                    <li><b>Render</b>
                        <p>Install <a href="https://embedthis.com/expansive/">Expansive</b></a>
                        and run <b>"expansive render"</b> to render the site into the "dist" directory.</p></li>

                    <li><b>Serve</b>
                        <p>Run <b>"esp -v"</b> or <b>"expansive"</b> to serve pages.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li><b>Browse</b>
                        <p>Navigate to <b>http://localhost:4000/</b> in your browser.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li><b>Generate Controllers</a></b>
                        <p>Create controllers to manage your app. Run 
                            <a href="https://embedthis.com/esp/doc/users/esp.html"><b>esp</b></a> 
                            with no options to see its usage.</p>
                        <pre>esp generate controller NAME [action, ...]</pre>
                    </li>

                    <li><b>Generate Scaffolds</a></b>
                        <p>Create entire scaffolds for large sections of your application. 
                        <pre>esp generate scaffold NAME [field:type, ...]</pre>
                    </li>
                    
                    <li><b>Read the Documentation</b>
                        <p>Go to <a href="https://embedthis.com/esp/doc/">
                        https://embedthis.com/esp/doc/</a> for the latest ESP documentation.
                        Here you can read quick tours, overviews and access all the ESP APIs.</b>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>Enjoy!</b></li>
                </ol>
            </section>
        </article>

